Name: autocreate_acl
Type: STRING
Default-Value: NULL
Last-Modified: 3.2.0
For-Documentation-Only: 1

If folders are to be created by *autocreate_inbox_folders*, this setting
can be used to apply additional ACLs to the autocreated folders.  The
syntax is "autocreate_acl folder identifier rights", where *folder* must
match one of the *autocreate_inbox_folders* folders, *identifier* must be a
valid cyrus identifier, and *rights* must be a valid cyrus rights string.
Multiple identifier|rights pairs can be assigned to a single folder by
providing this setting multiple times.

For example, "autocreate_acl Plus anyone p" would allow lmtp delivery to a
folder named "Plus".
